geneVariantDescriptions.description: KMT2A-TET1 results from the fusion of KMT2A and TET1 (PMID: 12124344, PMID: 12646957). KMT2A-TET1 has been identified in acute myeloid leukemia (PMID: 12124344, PMID: 12646957), B-cell precursor acute lymphoblastic leukemia (PMID: 19144982), and T-cell lymphoblastic lymphoma (PMID: 24323992), but has not been biochemically characterized and therefore, the effect on protein function is unknown (PubMed, Sep 2019).
